                    "description": "-From the end of 2001 until the beginning of 2005 I was the coordinator of PRI\u2019s research programme about the Gacaca jurisdictions in Rwanda. These jurisdictions can be seen as a highly decentralised system of participatory justice (a kind of reinvented traditional way of community based conflict resolution) to answer the justice problems Rwanda was facing after the genocide. PRI\u2019s research objectives were: To study the development and implementation of the Gacaca process and to document the whole process. PRI adopted a research-action approach and it had a social change agenda, such as to identify the problems and solutions together with the stakeholders (victims, perpetrators, population, authorities).\n- From 1998 until 2001 I was the head of a Programme of Support to the Prison Administration in Rwanda. Its objectives were the training of prison officers and personnel and the establishment and/or development of production activities in a selected number of prisons.",
